# Code organization

## Discover before you create (RAG)

Before adding a component, hook, server module, or schema:

1. Read `docs/CODE_INDEX.md` and search the codebase (`app/components/`, `app/lib/`, `app/server/`).
2. Reuse or extend existing code; do not duplicate UI, API wrappers, or providers.
3. If something is missing, add it in the **canonical location** and update `docs/CODE_INDEX.md`.

## Line budgets (soft limits)

| Layer | Target | If exceeded |
|-------|--------|---------------|
| `app/routes/*.tsx` | ≤150 lines | Extract to `app/components/` or `app/features/{name}/` |
| `app/components/*.tsx` | ≤200 lines | Split subcomponents into same folder |
| `app/server/*.ts` | ≤80 lines | Move logic to `app/lib/server/` |
| Route inline `createServerFn` | 0 preferred | Define in `app/server/{domain}.ts` |

Exceptions: generated files, thin re-exports, and legacy files under active refactor (note in PR).

## Layer responsibilities

```
routes/     → compose UI, wire loaders, no business logic
components/ → self-contained UI; props in, events out
features/   → route-specific bundles (optional): {components,hooks,schemas}.ts
server/     → createServerFn entrypoints only
lib/server/ → DB, OAuth, crypto, domain services
lib/        → schemas, queries, pure helpers, providers
```

## Self-contained components

- One primary export per file; colocate types unless shared.
- No fetching inside presentational components — use route loader, hook, or parent.
- Shared UI: `app/components/`. Feature-only UI: `app/features/{feature}/components/`.

## Reuse checklist (every PR)

- [ ] Searched for existing component/hook/server fn
- [ ] Route file stays compositional (imports + JSX)
- [ ] No duplicate zod schemas (use `app/lib/*-schemas.ts`)
- [ ] Updated `docs/CODE_INDEX.md` if new canonical module added
